The paper deals with channel estimation in intelligent reflecting surface (IRS) assisted communication systems, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the impact of massive MIMO on channel training time, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). Additionally, the paper proposes a pilot-based channel estimation method, which involves system-level design and optimization, making it relevant to systems and control (cs.SY) and computer communications (cs.COM).
